    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "\" To access a frozen key the user has to use either the pairing and PUK codes or the seed phrase.\" \r\n\r\nWell actually it's possible that user has two duplicates of the same card, so the frozen state is a qualification of the card and not of the account ....\r\nSo: I'd avoid greying out a keycard multiaccount\r\n\r\nWhen a user tries to tap a card with a PIN, he should always be shown the following: \r\n- if he's entered a wrong PIN, and has at least one more PIN attempt remaining: number of PIN attempts remaining\r\n-if he's entered a PIN but his card is PN blocked: he must be able to enter a PUK, and shown the number of PUK entry remaining if he made a wrong PUK entry attempt \r\n- if he's out of PIN & PUK entry : that his card is fully blocked. A geek could remove the applet and start everything from scratch but no through status. A regular status user should be let known that his card is bricked and he can't use it anymore at all. \r\n\r\n@andmironov ",
